
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [set-value] slot to modify the value of the [.sql] node. It concatenates a string to form an SQL statement that alters a table by adding a new column. The [strings.concat] slot combines static strings with the value retrieved from the [tableName] argument to construct the SQL command.
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat
      .:"alter table "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/tableName
      .:" add "
